{"word":"τάρβος","slug":"τάρβος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τάρβος</b></el> <el>(τάρβος, ος, εος, τό,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>fright, alarm, terror</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>awe, reverence</i>, <el>τινός</el> <i>for</i> one, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>an object of alarm, a fear, alarm</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}